{"id": "1479518061789839451", "channel_id": "1479475299237494888", "type": 0, "author_id": "693905974750216212", "author_name": "fishhazardthewizard", "author_bot": false, "content": "-# 我可以把我以前写的字也送到这里吗？https://discord.com/channels/1131791637933199470/1479428860591210528/1479513726377005168", "timestamp": "2026-03-06T16:36:34.047000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 3}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1479518469006561436", "channel_id": "1479475299237494888", "type": 19, "author_id": "977903961694674974", "author_name": "navirecorbeau", "author_bot": false, "content": "yes", "timestamp": "2026-03-06T16:38:11.135000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["693905974750216212"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🫶", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1479518061789839451", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1479518829171310644", "channel_id": "1479475299237494888", "type": 0, "author_id": "693905974750216212", "author_name": "fishhazardthewizard", "author_bot": false, "content": "As someone who’s been eagerly awaiting Arachne for a while now, please don’t change her design. Part of her charm was how her eyes looked a little tired and yet amused, like she was constantly observing/watching over everyone, and the new change gives us less of that, and more of  a younger-presenting character who is slightly amused. \nThe hat changing is a little understandable, but once again is a choice that makes her look younger again and less mysterious/enigmatic, which is another of her big draw factors for me.\nI don’t have the biggest objection with the clothing, as I do think the new art cleans it up quite a bit, but the artist giving her more cleavage is once again, detracting again a little from her charm, which did include the slight androgyny before.\nAll in all, I do still love her and I’ve already saved, so not much can be done about that, but these design adjustment choices have disappointed me as a longtime fan, and while I think I will eventually be able to adapt in time, much of her original charm has been lost through this artistic update.\n\nWhile yes, I do understand that and have no issues with the cleanups, the fact that they changed the vibes/feeling of the character almost completely through changing facial features/render is the part that bothers me, since a lot of my initial draw to her when they first released the 2.0 pv was a more mysterious looking character, with slight androgynous vibes and while she looked beautiful, was also definitely dangerous in some way. This adjusted version doesn’t portray the same character; she looks pretty, and that’s almost just it now. The slight adjustments have made her appear younger and more innocent, and by doing that, she’s just another pretty face.\nI’ve been drawing Arachne for almost 80 days in a row now, and been waiting for over a year. I’m not going to sugarcoat anything, and just am disappointed.\n<:bow:1356053037159944473> <:Helot_slack_off:1459092159465521184>", "timestamp": "2026-03-06T16:39:37.005000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "✅", "emoji_id": null, "count": 15}, {"emoji": "🫶", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
